# Session Context

- Always review relevant open files or recent edits at the start of a new session.
- Prioritize consistency with ROS 2 Humble, Gazebo Fortress, and ros2_control usage.
- Confirm controller manager naming and node duplication before running commands.

# File Scope Notes

Primary areas of work in this project:
- C++ core algorithms: `src/dog2_control/src/**/*.cpp`, `src/dog2_control/include/**/*.hpp`
- Simulation/description: `src/dog2_description/urdf/**/*.xacro`
- Configuration: `src/dog2_control/config/**/*.yaml`
- Python scripts: `src/dog2_motion_control/**/*.py`

# Safety and Validation

- When changing kinematics or gait parameters, verify workspace bounds and avoid unreachable targets.
- After edits, rebuild the relevant ROS 2 package and re-source the workspace.
